  "severity": "None",
  "overview": "An update for libvirt is now available for Red Hat Enterprise Linux 10.",
  "description": "Kernel-based Virtual Machine (KVM) offers a full virtualization solution forLinux on numerous hardware platforms. The virt:rhel module contains packageswhich provide user-space components used to run virtual machines using KVM.The packages also provide APIs for managing and interacting with the virtualized systems.Bug Fix(es) and Enhancement(s): Fix detection of existing vTPM when migrating [rhel-10.1.z] (JIRA:RHEL-132920)  Domain capabilities always reports TDX is supported [10.1.z] (JIRA:RHEL-129673)  Fail to get guest libvirtxml from VMware by virsh when datastore name has characters like '+' [rhel-10.1.z] (JIRA:RHEL-140465)  Virsh can't guest xml from VMware if guest's second disk is in sub-folder [rhel-10.1.z] (JIRA:RHEL-140865)",
